Ask HN: What is life like at a UARC?
text:
I have a PhD and was offered a position as a researcher at a UARC in the United States. UARCs are university affiliated research centers setup by the US DoD to act as a liaison between DoD and academia. However, after interviewing and speaking with a few employees of a competing UARC, these places seem like research dead-ends mostly acting like a glorified defense contractor.

I would like to do research and publish. HR tells me this is a great place to do these thing but when I check IEEE and Google scholar, i cant find any publications of authors from this institution. Plus, the interviews made it seem like the work is mostly doing data analysis or writing software. Nothing there lead me to believe I would be doing research day in and day out.

Does anyone on HN work for a UARC? Do you like it? How much research do you do?

title: Ask HN: Shopify 3rd party processor fee.. Questions
text:
Hello. I have a client that wants to use Shopify and also wants to use their current processor.

I can't get a straight answer from support.

Assume Advanced package for pricing. If someone uses a 3rd party processor does shopify apply their flat rate fee on top of the 3rd party fee?

The answer I got from support was yes they do. But this doesn't make sense because the 3rd party gateway would be tied to the processor which would apply their own fees and shopify is simply charging a fee of 0.5% to do that.

Online Canadian credit card rates -"2.4% + 30¢ CAD" ( this is a Flat rate Processing fee that shopify is passing on from their processor on to the store)

"3rd party fees on transactions not processed through Shopify Payments" - 0.5%

I can get my client cost + 0.05% which is still way cheaper with the 0.5% shopify fee.

So would my client be charged 2.4% + 30 cents + 0.5% + (processor cost) + 0.05% ?

If so this would be absurd.

Thank you.
